SopStream version 0.1.0
=====================

This script provides a simple way to start streaming P2P video
using the SopCast application.

It supports the ability to start streaming a channel by name, number
or URL (using the sop:// protocol).

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This script requires these other modules and libraries:

    Getopt::Long
    HTML::TreeBuilder
    IO::Socket
    LWP::UserAgent
    Pod::Usage
    Sys::Hostname

The script also requires the following to be installed on the target system:

    sp-sc
        SopCast P2P streaming video application for Linux (command line utility).
        Available from http://sopcast-player.googlecode.com/files/sp-auth-3.2.6.tar.gz
    
    libstdc++5
        The GNU Standard C++ Library v3 (dependency for sp-sc).
    

